[[File:Deathstar.jpg|thumb|right|220px|An [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] fires at a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[Rebel pilot/Legends|pilot]] emerging from the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star's]] Detention Block 2180.]]
'''Detention Block 2180''' was a prisoner detainment area on the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]]. It was located in proximity to the battle station's [[Superlaser Fire Control]] Room and to the [[Hangar 84G|Hangars 84G]] and [[Hangar 85G|85G]].<ref name="BFII" />

At the very beginning of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], this block held prisoners of war associated with the early [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]]. In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], when the battle station was in the final phases of construction, a [[Death Star prisoner|Jedi]] being held with the other Rebels devised a plan to help the inmates escape the station in a [[Death Star Uprising|quickly growing uprising]]. However, the [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] of the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]] managed to put down the riot, killing or capturing all the escaped prisoners.<ref name="BFII" />

